<br>
Your (the magician's tower) board is incredibly hostile. There's no way someone can post something on your board that differ from your usual whining without getting flamed, often with no regard to the actual content of the post. I don't think I ever reacted this way in a discussion but I am really disgusted.<br>
<br>
That and you guys lack in reading comprehension or don't take the time to even read what I am writing.<br>
<br>
Never at any point was I complaining that dire charm or AE groups were underpowered. They are great.<br>
<br>
I am just pointing out how they work exactly, and why they aren't as powerful as some people would have it. If they need to be nerfed I don't care and that wasn't really my point. I just wanted to get the facts straight because most of the posters here don't know enough to comment on these things.<br>
<br>
It is my perception that outside of these two abilities, that level 60 enchanters pretty much suck. You can agree or disagree with me, and we can debate this to no end, or we can agree to disagree. <br>
<br>
I just wanted to point out that no you don't get 2 orange an hour of AA soloing with dire charm, and also that no I don't log in and immeditately start Aeing until I log off. <br>
<br>
If you want these abilities to be nerfed, at least get proper sense of how they scale up, and get a clue of what the level 60 game is before ranting. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
